               <history>
                 <origin>
                    <origDate xml:lang="ar">غالبا ١٨٩٧-١٩٢٧</origDate>
                    <origDate notBefore="1897" notAfter="1927">Most likely 1897–1927</origDate>.
                    <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13380Qerellos"><hi rendition="simple:italic">ʾAbbā</hi> Qerǝllos</persName>, mentioned as <foreign xml:lang="gez">
               አባ፡ ቄርሎስ፡ ዘሀገር፡ አባይ፡ እለ፡ እስክንድርያ፡</foreign> on <locus target="#2r">fol. 2r</locus>, might be
             <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3259CyrilV">Patriarch Cyril V </persName> (in tenure <date>1874–1927</date>).
                    The identity of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13378Serabamon">Bishop Sǝrābāmon</persName>, mentioned on <locus target="#2r">fol. 2r</locus>
                    (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ወዲበ፡ ርእሰ፡ ሀገር፡ አበዊነ፡ ብፁእ፡ ጳጳስ፡ አባ፡ ስራባሞን፡</foreign>),
                    is uncertain. He could be <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13377YuhannaAsnawi">Yuḥannā al-ʾAsnāwī</persName>, a head of <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0478DS">Dayr as-Suryān</placeName>
            who was consecrated the bishop of the Sudan with the name
            Ṣarābāmūn in 1897. The text also mentions <foreign xml:lang="gez"><t:roleName xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="title"><hi rendition="simple:italic">ʾAbuna</hi></t:roleName> Lǝqʷās (sic for Luqās?)</foreign>
         on <locus target="#1v">fol. 1v</locus>, who is difficult to identify. A later dating, to the time of the Coptic
                    <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3260CyrilVI">patriarch Cyril VI</persName> (in tenure <time><date>1959–1971</date></time>), is less probable.

                    <hi rendition="simple:smallcaps">MSS</hi> <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/DSEthiop20">DS Ethiop. 20</ref>,
          <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/DSEthiop17">DS Ethiop. 17</ref> and
                    <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/DSEthiop24">DS Ethiop. 24</ref>
                    belong together; they are
          probably parts of an unfinished manuscript begun in
          <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC2804Egypt">Egypt</placeName>.</origin>
               </history>

